// You are given three candidate solutions to a problem with n up to 2*10^5.
// Time limit: 2 seconds.
// Determine which solutions will PASS (AC) and which will TLE.
//
// Solution A: Two nested loops, each from 0 to n. O(n^2)
// Solution B: Sort + single binary search per query (q queries, q <= n). O((n+q) log n)
// Solution C: Three nested loops each 0..sqrt(n). O(n * sqrt(n))
//
// Estimate the number of operations for n = 2*10^5 and determine AC/TLE.

